### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core, elements

### Is this a regression?

Yes

### Description

When component with hostDirective is converted into a custom element using @angular/elements package input/outputs of hostdirective are not honoured. So there is no way to initialize these inputs/outputs which are defined in host directive.

consider you have following directive and component
```
@Directive({
  selector: '[appExampleHost]',
  standalone: true,
})
export class ExampleHostDirective implements AfterViewInit {
  @Input() hostDirectiveInput!: string;
  constructor() {}

  ngAfterViewInit() {
    console.log('printing host directive input ' + this.hostDirectiveInput);
  }
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-host-component',
  templateUrl: './host-component.component.html',
  standalone: true,
  hostDirectives: [{
    directive: ExampleHostDirective,
    inputs: ['hostDirectiveInput: hostDirectiveInput']
  }]
})
export class HostComponentComponent  {}
```

and if you convert `HostComponentComponent` into custom element using `@angular/elements` and use it like this
```
<app-host-webcomponent hostDirectiveInput="Angular Rocks"></app-host-webcomponent>
```

the `ExampleHostDirective` will initialize but will not have input set to 'Angular Rocks'



