### Which @angular/* package(s) are relevant/related to the feature request?

core

### Description

It would be a great addition if the `@for` block would support the `@loading` block with the same functionality as on the `@defer` block.
This would be useful for cases where data is loaded asynchronously.

### Proposed solution

Very simple example:
```js
@for (entry of entries | async; track entry.id) {
  <p>{{ entry.title }}</p>
} @loading (minimum 200ms) {
  <p>Loading</p>
} @empty {
  <p>No entries</p>
}
```

### Alternatives considered

I tried using the `@defer` block, but that didn't work as intended:
```js
@defer {
  @for (entry of entries | async; track entry.id) {
    <p>{{ entry.title }}</p>
  } @empty {
    <p>No entries</p>
  }
} @placeholder (minimum 200ms) {
  <p>Loading</p>
}
```

